{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Eph|5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","chapter":5,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":1,"text":"Therefore, be imitators of God, as dearly loved children,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":2,"text":"and walk in love, as Christ also loved us and gave himself for us, a sacrificial and fragrant offering to God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":3,"text":"But sexual immorality and any impurity or greed should not even be heard of among you, as is proper for saints.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":4,"text":"Obscene and foolish talking or crude joking are not suitable, but rather giving thanks.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":5,"text":"For know and recognize this: Every sexually immoral or impure or greedy person, who is an idolater, does not have an inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":6,"text":"Let no one deceive you with empty arguments, for God’s wrath is coming on the disobedient because of these things.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":7,"text":"Therefore, do not become their partners.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":8,"text":"For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Walk as children of light —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":9,"text":"for the fruit of the light consists of all goodness, righteousness, and truth —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":10,"text":"testing what is pleasing to the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":11,"text":"Don’t participate in the fruitless works of darkness, but instead expose them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":12,"text":"For it is shameful even to mention what is done by them in secret.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":13,"text":"Everything exposed by the light is made visible,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":14,"text":"for what makes everything visible is light. Therefore it is said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":15,"text":"Pay careful attention, then, to how you walk —not as unwise people but as wise —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":16,"text":"making the most of the time, because the days are evil.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":17,"text":"So don’t be foolish, but understand what the Lord’s will is.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":18,"text":"And don’t get drunk with wine, which leads to reckless living, but be filled by the Spirit:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":19,"text":"speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, singing and making music with your heart to the Lord,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":20,"text":"giving thanks always for everything to God the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":21,"text":"submitting to one another in the fear of Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":22,"text":"Wives, submit to your husbands as to the Lord,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":23,"text":"because the husband is the head of the wife as Christ is the head of the church. He is the Savior of the body.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":24,"text":"Now as the church submits to Christ, so also wives are to submit to their husbands in everything.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":25,"text":"Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ loved the church and gave himself for her","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":26,"text":"to make her holy, cleansing her with the washing of water by the word.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":27,"text":"He did this to present the church to himself in splendor, without spot or wrinkle or anything like that, but holy and blameless.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":28,"text":"In the same way, husbands are to love their wives as their own bodies. He who loves his wife loves himself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":29,"text":"For no one ever hates his own flesh but provides and cares for it, just as Christ does for the church,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":30,"text":"since we are members of his body.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":31,"text":"For this reason a man will leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and the two will become one flesh.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":32,"text":"This mystery is profound, but I am talking about Christ and the church.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","bookOrder":48,"chapter":5,"verse":33,"text":"To sum up, each one of you is to love his wife as himself, and the wife is to respect her husband.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Eph","chapter":5,"paragraphStarts":[1,6,15,22],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":6,"text":"Light versus Darkness"},{"beforeVerse":15,"text":"Consistency in the Christian Life"},{"beforeVerse":22,"text":"Wives and Husbands"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Therefore, be imitators of God, as dearly loved children, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and walk in love, as Christ also loved us and gave himself for us, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Th 2:13","book":"2Th","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 2:14","book":"Tit","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" a sacrificial and fragrant offering to God. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Th 2:13","book":"2Th","chapter":2,"verse":13},{"label":"Ti 2:14","book":"Tit","chapter":2,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Eph:5:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But sexual immorality "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Th 4:3","book":"1Th","chapter":4,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and any impurity "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Th 4:7","book":"1Th","chapter":4,